events.title: Ann Arbor RFFA Canvass
events.description:
Join us for our next big action as we start door knocking in different locations all around the state! We'll be heading out to the doors to get voters engaged about the upcoming election and making sure this ballot initiative has enough votes to pass in November.
 
The United States Supreme Court issued an opinion in Jackson Women’s Health Organization v. Dobbs and overturned Roe v. Wade.

Important medical decisions should be guided by a patient's health and wellbeing, not by a politician's beliefs. But for too long, politicians across the country have been fighting to restrict reproductive health care, and now they are gaining ground.

If the U.S. Supreme Court overturns Roe v. Wade, an abortion ban from 1931 could go back into effect in Michigan, cutting off access to abortion for more than 2 million Michiganders and threatening doctors with prison.

Reproductive Freedom for All is a campaign to amend the Michigan Constitution. Our amendment would guarantee the right to reproductive freedom for all, and make sure Lansing politicians cannot interfere in our personal decisions.

Specifically, our proposal will affirm that every person has the fundamental right to reproductive freedom, which involves the right to make and carry out decisions without political interference about all matters relating to pregnancy, including birth control, abortion, infertility, miscarriage care, prenatal care, and childbirth.

Sign up today to help protect reproductive freedom in Michigan.

events.title: Write Letters and Postcards to Voters with A2D2 Swing Left!
events.description:
Join us on the evening of Wednesday, September 21st, as we write to voters! 
 
Work with **Vote Forward** to write to a infrequent voters and tell them why you are a voter. Receipt of a personally addressed letter with a clear message is shown to increase voter turnout. 

Or write postcards to Michigan Dems in important Congressional Districts with **Postcards to Swing States**.

RSVP here, and we’ll let you know how to join this party. Invite your friends, too.   

Think about it: if you help get a voter to the polls, that is an important step towards creating a more inclusive and equitable government and society. 

Looking forward to seeing you!
